Dialogue: 0,0:04:18.15,0:04:24.65,注,,0,0,0,,Androgynous Peripheral Attach System(APAS)\N异体同构周边式对接系统
Dialogue: 0,0:04:49.12,0:04:56.91,注,,0,0,0,,国际对接适配器 IDA
Dialogue: 0,0:04:57.46,0:05:03.58,注,,0,0,0,,av437185351 16分开始
Dialogue: 0,0:06:46.62,0:06:53.27,注,,0,0,0,,曙光号功能货仓在1998年11月由俄罗斯质子号火箭发射
Dialogue: 0,0:11:43.03,0:11:50.82,注,,0,0,0,,PDGF: 电力和数据传输型锚钩固定装置
Dialogue: 0,0:00:01.03,0:00:07.40,注,,0,0,0,,av41754103 国际空间站建造过程3D动画介绍
Dialogue: 1,0:00:01.03,0:00:05.24,中,,0,0,0,,2018年 我制作了一期视频介绍国际空间站
Dialogue: 2,0:00:01.03,0:00:05.24,英,,0,0,0,,In 2018, I made an animation about the International Space Station.
Dialogue: 1,0:00:05.44,0:00:07.40,中,,0,0,0,,带大家了解各个部件的组装顺序
Dialogue: 2,0:00:05.44,0:00:07.40,英,,0,0,0,,I showed all the pieces coming together,
Dialogue: 1,0:00:07.40,0:00:09.45,中,,0,0,0,,但其中并没有介绍具体的建造方法
Dialogue: 2,0:00:07.40,0:00:09.45,英,,0,0,0,,but I didn't show how it was done.
Dialogue: 1,0:00:10.30,0:00:12.81,中,,0,0,0,,这些舱段并不是自己飞过去完成对接组装的
Dialogue: 2,0:00:10.30,0:00:12.81,英,,0,0,0,,These modules didn't just float together on their own.
Dialogue: 1,0:00:12.81,0:00:14.04,中,,0,0,0,,实际的工作量相当大
Dialogue: 2,0:00:12.81,0:00:14.04,英,,0,0,0,,It was a lot of work.
Dialogue: 1,0:00:14.90,0:00:17.24,中,,0,0,0,,任务涉及到地面的任务控制中心
Dialogue: 2,0:00:14.90,0:00:17.24,英,,0,0,0,,It involved mission controllers back on Earth,
Dialogue: 1,0:00:17.48,0:00:21.64,中,,0,0,0,,空间站上的宇航员 和一些精巧的机器人
Dialogue: 2,0:00:17.48,0:00:21.64,英,,0,0,0,,astronauts onboard the station, and some fancy robotics.
Dialogue: 1,0:00:22.23,0:00:26.01,中,,0,0,0,,本期视频我们将深入了解这些任务是如何完成的
Dialogue: 2,0:00:22.23,0:00:26.01,英,,0,0,0,,In this video, we're gonna dive deep into the details to see how it worked.
Dialogue: 1,0:00:37.44,0:00:41.07,中,,0,0,0,,国际空间站的建造工作花费超过十年
Dialogue: 2,0:00:37.44,0:00:41.07,英,,0,0,0,,The International Space Station took over a decade to complete.
Dialogue: 1,0:00:45.24,0:00:48.91,中,,0,0,0,,画面中的多数部件都是由这样的航天飞机发射上去的
Dialogue: 2,0:00:45.24,0:00:48.91,英,,0,0,0,,Most of the pieces that you see here were launched by this space shuttle.
Dialogue: 1,0:00:49.96,0:00:52.92,中,,0,0,0,,实际上 这也正是航天飞机的主要功能
Dialogue: 2,0:00:49.96,0:00:52.92,英,,0,0,0,,In fact, this was one of the main purposes of the space shuttle.
Dialogue: 1,0:00:52.92,0:00:54.84,中,,0,0,0,,——建设空间站
Dialogue: 2,0:00:52.92,0:00:54.84,英,,0,0,0,,It was to build the space station.
Dialogue: 1,0:00:55.45,0:00:57.42,中,,0,0,0,,我们无法把每个任务都过一遍
Dialogue: 2,0:00:55.45,0:00:57.42,英,,0,0,0,,We can't go over every single mission.
Dialogue: 1,0:00:57.42,0:00:59.32,中,,0,0,0,,这样视频就太长了
Dialogue: 2,0:00:57.42,0:00:59.32,英,,0,0,0,,That would take too long for this video.
Dialogue: 1,0:00:59.55,0:01:03.33,中,,0,0,0,,我想介绍国际空间站建设的初始阶段
Dialogue: 2,0:00:59.55,0:01:03.33,英,,0,0,0,,What I'd like to do is talk about the initial stages of the station's construction
Dialogue: 1,0:01:03.33,0:01:05.47,中,,0,0,0,,那时还是国际空间站的幼年时期
Dialogue: 2,0:01:03.33,0:01:05.47,英,,0,0,0,,back when the ISS was really small.
Dialogue: 1,0:01:05.85,0:01:09.99,中,,0,0,0,,我们将回顾几个航天飞机任务 了解这些舱段与组件的组装方法
Dialogue: 2,0:01:05.85,0:01:09.99,英,,0,0,0,,We'll go over just a few of the space shuttle missions and how these pieces were put together.
Dialogue: 1,0:01:16.83,0:01:21.07,中,,0,0,0,,空间站不是在茫茫太空中悬停在那里的
Dialogue: 2,0:01:16.83,0:01:21.07,英,,0,0,0,,We've got to remember, the station isn't just aimlessly floating in space.
Dialogue: 1,0:01:21.07,0:01:23.24,中,,0,0,0,,而是以极高速度在运动
Dialogue: 2,0:01:21.07,0:01:23.24,英,,0,0,0,,It's going incredibly fast,
Dialogue: 1,0:01:23.24,0:01:26.44,中,,0,0,0,,大约是地面音速的20多倍
Dialogue: 2,0:01:23.24,0:01:26.44,英,,0,0,0,,about 20 times the speed of sound here on Earth.
Dialogue: 1,0:01:27.11,0:01:29.84,中,,0,0,0,,每90分钟绕地球一圈
Dialogue: 2,0:01:27.11,0:01:29.84,英,,0,0,0,,It orbits the earth once every 90 minutes.
Dialogue: 1,0:01:32.01,0:01:35.67,中,,0,0,0,,视频所示是空间站的"前向" 即它的运行方向
Dialogue: 2,0:01:32.01,0:01:35.67,英,,0,0,0,,Here's the front of the station. It always travels in this direction.
Dialogue: 1,0:01:35.91,0:01:39.29,中,,0,0,0,,前向 后向 左舷 右舷
Dialogue: 2,0:01:35.91,0:01:39.29,英,,0,0,0,,So this is forward, and aft, port and starboard,
Dialogue: 1,0:01:39.29,0:01:41.87,中,,0,0,0,,径向向外 指向远离地球的方向
Dialogue: 2,0:01:39.29,0:01:41.87,英,,0,0,0,,and then there's zenith pointing away from the earth,
Dialogue: 1,0:01:41.87,0:01:44.01,中,,0,0,0,,径向向内 指向地球
Dialogue: 2,0:01:41.87,0:01:44.01,英,,0,0,0,,and nadir pointing towards the earth.
Dialogue: 1,0:01:44.90,0:01:48.02,中,,0,0,0,,这些都是宇航员常用的词汇
Dialogue: 2,0:01:44.90,0:01:48.02,英,,0,0,0,,These terms are part of the regular vocabulary of an astronaut.
Dialogue: 1,0:01:48.02,0:01:50.29,中,,0,0,0,,本期视频之后也会稍稍提到
Dialogue: 2,0:01:48.02,0:01:50.29,英,,0,0,0,,We'll be using them a little bit throughout this video.
Dialogue: 1,0:01:50.91,0:01:53.45,中,,0,0,0,,完工后的国际空间站长这样
Dialogue: 2,0:01:50.91,0:01:53.45,英,,0,0,0,,This is what the completed station looks like.
Dialogue: 1,0:01:53.63,0:01:57.48,中,,0,0,0,,宇航员只能在加压舱段内生活
Dialogue: 2,0:01:53.63,0:01:57.48,英,,0,0,0,,The only part that the astronauts can live in are the pressurized modules.
Dialogue: 1,0:01:57.64,0:02:02.13,中,,0,0,0,,"舱段" 指画面中空间站的圆柱体部分
Dialogue: 2,0:01:57.64,0:02:02.13,英,,0,0,0,,When I say module, I'm referring to one of these cylindrical pieces of the space station.
Dialogue: 1,0:02:03.19,0:02:06.07,中,,0,0,0,,其中有空气可供呼吸 有舒适的生存环境
Dialogue: 2,0:02:03.19,0:02:06.07,英,,0,0,0,,It has air to breathe, comfortable living conditions,
Dialogue: 1,0:02:06.07,0:02:09.10,中,,0,0,0,,可以让宇航员免于暴露在真空中
Dialogue: 2,0:02:06.07,0:02:09.10,英,,0,0,0,,and protects the astronauts from the vacuum of space.
Dialogue: 1,0:02:09.79,0:02:12.36,中,,0,0,0,,每个舱段都有一个或多个停泊口
Dialogue: 2,0:02:09.79,0:02:12.36,英,,0,0,0,,Each module has one or more berthing ports
Dialogue: 1,0:02:12.36,0:02:14.70,中,,0,0,0,,可以与其他舱段连接
Dialogue: 2,0:02:12.36,0:02:14.70,英,,0,0,0,,that can be connected to other parts of the station.
Dialogue: 1,0:02:14.70,0:02:17.43,中,,0,0,0,,有时称为"对接口"
Dialogue: 2,0:02:14.70,0:02:17.43,英,,0,0,0,,Sometimes these are referred to as docking ports,
Dialogue: 1,0:02:17.43,0:02:19.88,中,,0,0,0,,但具体来讲 它应该叫停泊口
Dialogue: 2,0:02:17.43,0:02:19.88,英,,0,0,0,,but if we're being specific, it is a berthing port
Dialogue: 1,0:02:19.88,0:02:24.55,中,,0,0,0,,因为舱段或飞船需要机械臂的辅助才能对接
Dialogue: 2,0:02:19.88,0:02:24.55,英,,0,0,0,,because the joining module or spacecraft must be assisted by use of a robotic arm.
Dialogue: 1,0:02:27.58,0:02:30.07,中,,0,0,0,,空间站舱段主要分为两大部分
Dialogue: 2,0:02:27.58,0:02:30.07,英,,0,0,0,,There are two main sections to the station,
Dialogue: 1,0:02:30.25,0:02:33.32,中,,0,0,0,,来自俄罗斯的俄罗斯舱段
Dialogue: 2,0:02:30.25,0:02:33.32,英,,0,0,0,,the Russian orbital segment, these are modules from Russia,
Dialogue: 1,0:02:33.62,0:02:35.96,中,,0,0,0,,和来自美国 欧洲 日本的美国舱段
Dialogue: 2,0:02:33.62,0:02:35.96,英,,0,0,0,,and the United States orbital segment,
Dialogue: 1,0:02:35.96,0:02:40.01,中,,0,0,0,,和来自美国 欧洲 日本的美国舱段
Dialogue: 2,0:02:35.96,0:02:40.01,英,,0,0,0,,these are modules from the United States, Europe, and Japan.
Dialogue: 1,0:02:41.05,0:02:44.73,中,,0,0,0,,可以注意到两边舱段外观上的些许不同
Dialogue: 2,0:02:41.05,0:02:44.73,英,,0,0,0,,You can see how the modules on each side look just a little bit different.
Dialogue: 1,0:02:45.40,0:02:51.08,中,,0,0,0,,在美国段 舱段之间使用通用停泊机构(CBM)连接
Dialogue: 2,0:02:45.40,0:02:51.08,英,,0,0,0,,On the US side, the modules are connected by the common berthing mechanism, or CBM for short.
Dialogue: 1,0:02:51.67,0:02:56.07,中,,0,0,0,,CBM分两种 主动侧和被动侧
Dialogue: 2,0:02:51.67,0:02:56.07,英,,0,0,0,,There are two different sides to this, the active side and the passive side.
Dialogue: 1,0:02:57.04,0:03:00.17,中,,0,0,0,,两侧对接后 插销会将双方拉近
Dialogue: 2,0:02:57.04,0:03:00.17,英,,0,0,0,,Once these are brought together, latches pull them in close,
Dialogue: 1,0:03:00.17,0:03:03.50,中,,0,0,0,,之后会有16个螺栓将两者紧紧固定起来
Dialogue: 2,0:03:00.17,0:03:03.50,英,,0,0,0,,and then there are 16 bolts to firmly mate them together.
Dialogue: 1,0:03:05.33,0:03:07.76,中,,0,0,0,,两者中间的空间称为"前室"
Dialogue: 2,0:03:05.33,0:03:07.76,英,,0,0,0,,The space in between is called the vestibule.
Dialogue: 1,0:03:07.76,0:03:09.66,中,,0,0,0,,这里会用空气加压
Dialogue: 2,0:03:07.76,0:03:09.66,英,,0,0,0,,This will be pressurized with air.
Dialogue: 1,0:03:09.66,0:03:11.39,中,,0,0,0,,需要花费几个小时
Dialogue: 2,0:03:09.66,0:03:11.39,英,,0,0,0,,This process takes a few hours.
Dialogue: 1,0:03:11.67,0:03:14.66,中,,0,0,0,,然后舱门开启 移除一些设施
Dialogue: 2,0:03:11.67,0:03:14.66,英,,0,0,0,,Then the hatch is opened, some of the hardware is removed,
Dialogue: 1,0:03:14.66,0:03:19.63,中,,0,0,0,,再接好氧气 电力 数据与水等
Dialogue: 2,0:03:14.66,0:03:19.63,英,,0,0,0,,and connections are made in between the modules, which includes oxygen, power, data, and water.
Dialogue: 1,0:03:20.04,0:03:23.53,中,,0,0,0,,完成后 再用白色保护罩围上
Dialogue: 2,0:03:20.04,0:03:23.53,英,,0,0,0,,Once finalized, there is a white protective barrier put in place.
Dialogue: 1,0:03:24.00,0:03:27.23,中,,0,0,0,,宇航员就能自由穿行两个舱段了
Dialogue: 2,0:03:24.00,0:03:27.23,英,,0,0,0,,The astronauts can now move freely in between the modules.
Dialogue: 1,0:03:28.17,0:03:32.25,中,,0,0,0,,通用停泊机构用于两个永久连接的舱段之间
Dialogue: 2,0:03:28.17,0:03:32.25,英,,0,0,0,,The common berthing mechanism is used for modules that are permanently attached together,
Dialogue: 1,0:03:32.25,0:03:34.44,中,,0,0,0,,比如协和号节点舱与命运号实验舱
Dialogue: 2,0:03:32.25,0:03:34.44,英,,0,0,0,,like the Harmony and Destiny modules.
Dialogue: 1,0:03:35.14,0:03:39.69,中,,0,0,0,,还可用来服务来访的航天器 比如SpaceX的货运龙飞船
Dialogue: 2,0:03:35.14,0:03:39.69,英,,0,0,0,,They can also be used for visiting spacecraft such as the SpaceX Cargo Dragon.
Dialogue: 1,0:03:41.58,0:03:46.47,中,,0,0,0,,俄罗斯舱段使用的对接机构与CBM并不适配
Dialogue: 2,0:03:41.58,0:03:46.47,英,,0,0,0,,The Russian side of the station uses a different docking mechanism that is not compatible with CBM.
Dialogue: 1,0:03:46.90,0:03:49.39,中,,0,0,0,,所以我们需要想办法连接两种不同的机构
Dialogue: 2,0:03:46.90,0:03:49.39,英,,0,0,0,,We need some way to connect to the different mechanisms.
Dialogue: 1,0:03:49.72,0:03:53.08,中,,0,0,0,,类似于把美标的电器插头带到欧洲
Dialogue: 2,0:03:49.72,0:03:53.08,英,,0,0,0,,This is kind of like taking a power plug from the United States
Dialogue: 1,0:03:53.08,0:03:54.90,中,,0,0,0,,类似于把美标的电器插头带到欧洲
Dialogue: 2,0:03:53.08,0:03:54.90,英,,0,0,0,,and bringing it over to Europe.
Dialogue: 1,0:03:55.50,0:03:57.42,中,,0,0,0,,美标的插头插不进欧标的墙插
Dialogue: 2,0:03:55.50,0:03:57.42,英,,0,0,0,,It's not compatible with the wall plug.
Dialogue: 1,0:03:57.70,0:03:59.85,中,,0,0,0,,需要什么呢? 适配器
Dialogue: 2,0:03:57.70,0:03:59.85,英,,0,0,0,,What do we need? An adapter.
Dialogue: 1,0:04:00.76,0:04:04.26,中,,0,0,0,,国际空间站上也一样 只是尺寸更大一点
Dialogue: 2,0:04:00.76,0:04:04.26,英,,0,0,0,,It's the same concept on the space station, but on a larger scale.
Dialogue: 1,0:04:04.26,0:04:07.76,中,,0,0,0,,两种不同机构 中间需要适配器来连接
Dialogue: 2,0:04:04.26,0:04:07.76,英,,0,0,0,,Two different mechanisms, so we need an adapter in between.
Dialogue: 1,0:04:07.90,0:04:12.22,中,,0,0,0,,这个适配器叫"加压对接适配舱" 简称PMA
Dialogue: 2,0:04:07.90,0:04:12.22,英,,0,0,0,,This is called the pressurized mating adapter, or PMA for short.
Dialogue: 1,0:04:12.78,0:04:17.16,中,,0,0,0,,大头侧使用CBM 可以连接空间站的美国段
Dialogue: 2,0:04:12.78,0:04:17.16,英,,0,0,0,,The larger side uses CBM, which can be attached to the US side of the station.
Dialogue: 1,0:04:18.15,0:04:20.46,中,,0,0,0,,小头侧使用APAS
Dialogue: 2,0:04:18.15,0:04:20.46,英,,0,0,0,,The smaller side uses APAS.
Dialogue: 1,0:04:20.46,0:04:24.65,中,,0,0,0,,它可以连接俄罗斯侧的舱段和航天飞机
Dialogue: 2,0:04:20.46,0:04:24.65,英,,0,0,0,,This is compatible with the Russian side of the station and with the space shuttle.
Dialogue: 1,0:04:29.66,0:04:32.91,中,,0,0,0,,截至目前 国际空间站上共有三个PMA
Dialogue: 2,0:04:29.66,0:04:32.91,英,,0,0,0,,On this station today, there are three of these adapters.
Dialogue: 1,0:04:33.26,0:04:37.22,中,,0,0,0,,PMA-1用于美国段与俄罗斯段之间的永久连接
Dialogue: 2,0:04:33.26,0:04:37.22,英,,0,0,0,,PMA-1 is permanently in place connecting the two sides of the station.
Dialogue: 1,0:04:37.22,0:04:41.38,中,,0,0,0,,PMA-2与PMA-3用于对接航天飞机
Dialogue: 2,0:04:37.22,0:04:41.38,英,,0,0,0,,PMA-2 and PMA-3 were used as docking ports for the space shuttle.
Dialogue: 1,0:04:41.60,0:04:46.24,中,,0,0,0,,它的小头侧 使用APAS 用来连接航天飞机
Dialogue: 2,0:04:41.60,0:04:46.24,英,,0,0,0,,The smaller side, which is the side that uses APAS, was used for the space shuttle.
Dialogue: 1,0:04:46.46,0:04:48.72,中,,0,0,0,,航天飞机就是使用它与空间站对接的
Dialogue: 2,0:04:46.46,0:04:48.72,英,,0,0,0,,This is how it would dock to the space station.
Dialogue: 1,0:04:49.12,0:04:53.57,中,,0,0,0,,这两个PMA末端现在都加装了另外一种适配器
Dialogue: 2,0:04:49.12,0:04:53.57,英,,0,0,0,,Both of these PMAs now have yet another type of adapter placed at the end.
Dialogue: 1,0:04:53.57,0:04:56.91,中,,0,0,0,,让现代航天器有能力与国际空间站对接
Dialogue: 2,0:04:53.57,0:04:56.91,英,,0,0,0,,This allows for more modern spacecraft to dock to the space station.
Dialogue: 1,0:04:57.46,0:05:01.42,中,,0,0,0,,这部分的详细内容可以观看之前介绍载人龙飞船的视频
Dialogue: 2,0:04:57.46,0:05:01.42,英,,0,0,0,,If you'd like to see this in action, you can watch my SpaceX Crew Dragon video.
Dialogue: 1,0:05:01.52,0:05:03.58,中,,0,0,0,,视频链接在下方
Dialogue: 2,0:05:01.52,0:05:03.58,英,,0,0,0,,I'll leave a link in the description below.
Dialogue: 1,0:05:05.14,0:05:07.68,中,,0,0,0,,我们快速介绍一下航天飞机
Dialogue: 2,0:05:05.14,0:05:07.68,英,,0,0,0,,Now, let's take a quick look at this space shuttle.
Dialogue: 1,0:05:08.95,0:05:12.61,中,,0,0,0,,乘组多数时间在机组舱内
Dialogue: 2,0:05:08.95,0:05:12.61,英,,0,0,0,,The crew spends most of their time up here in the crew compartment.
Dialogue: 1,0:05:14.29,0:05:16.37,中,,0,0,0,,后部是载荷舱
Dialogue: 2,0:05:14.29,0:05:16.37,英,,0,0,0,,Back here is the payload bay.
Dialogue: 1,0:05:16.46,0:05:19.74,中,,0,0,0,,空间站的舱段就是放在这里发射进入太空的
Dialogue: 2,0:05:16.46,0:05:19.74,英,,0,0,0,,This is where the space station modules were carried up into space.
Dialogue: 1,0:05:20.98,0:05:23.53,中,,0,0,0,,前部是轨道对接系统
Dialogue: 2,0:05:20.98,0:05:23.53,英,,0,0,0,,Up front here is the orbital docking system.
Dialogue: 1,0:05:23.82,0:05:26.87,中,,0,0,0,,航天飞机通过这里与国际空间站对接
Dialogue: 2,0:05:23.82,0:05:26.87,英,,0,0,0,,This is the place they could dock to the International Space Station.
Dialogue: 1,0:05:27.67,0:05:31.19,中,,0,0,0,,宇航员还可以通过侧面这个舱门进行出舱行走
Dialogue: 2,0:05:27.67,0:05:31.19,英,,0,0,0,,The astronauts can also do spacewalks from out of this hatch.
Dialogue: 1,0:05:35.02,0:05:37.17,中,,0,0,0,,侧面这里是加拿大臂
Dialogue: 2,0:05:35.02,0:05:37.17,英,,0,0,0,,On the side here is the Canadarm.
Dialogue: 1,0:05:37.41,0:05:41.19,中,,0,0,0,,可以在太空中抓取并移动设备
Dialogue: 2,0:05:37.41,0:05:41.19,英,,0,0,0,,It's a robotic arm that is capable of moving things around in space.
Dialogue: 1,0:05:41.78,0:05:45.99,中,,0,0,0,,机械臂可以由画面中航天飞机的工作台操控
Dialogue: 2,0:05:41.78,0:05:45.99,英,,0,0,0,,The arm can be controlled from inside of the space shuttle at this workstation.
Dialogue: 1,0:05:48.11,0:05:51.95,中,,0,0,0,,航天飞机从佛罗里达州的肯尼迪航天中心发射升空
Dialogue: 2,0:05:48.11,0:05:51.95,英,,0,0,0,,The space shuttle launches took place from Kennedy Space Center in Florida.
Dialogue: 1,0:05:55.17,0:05:57.87,中,,0,0,0,,进入太空后 载荷舱舱门开启
Dialogue: 2,0:05:55.17,0:05:57.87,英,,0,0,0,,Once in space, the payload bay doors were opened.
Dialogue: 1,0:05:57.87,0:06:01.03,中,,0,0,0,,并在整个太空飞行中一直保持开启
Dialogue: 2,0:05:57.87,0:06:01.03,英,,0,0,0,,They remained open for the entire time they were in space.
Dialogue: 1,0:06:02.15,0:06:06.20,中,,0,0,0,,之后航天飞机会花几天时间追上国际空间站
Dialogue: 2,0:06:02.15,0:06:06.20,英,,0,0,0,,Then it took a few days for the space shuttle to catch up with the ISS.
Dialogue: 1,0:06:07.09,0:06:12.42,中,,0,0,0,,航天飞机如今已退役 但它在国际空间站的建设中发挥了关键作用
Dialogue: 2,0:06:07.09,0:06:12.42,英,,0,0,0,,The space shuttle is retired now, but it played a crucial role in building the space station.
Dialogue: 1,0:06:13.10,0:06:15.99,中,,0,0,0,,我们来了解航天飞机其中几次任务
Dialogue: 2,0:06:13.10,0:06:15.99,英,,0,0,0,,Let's take a look at a few of these space shuttle missions.
Dialogue: 1,0:06:16.34,0:06:19.14,中,,0,0,0,,第一个任务我们会讲得详细一点
Dialogue: 2,0:06:16.34,0:06:19.14,英,,0,0,0,,This first mission we'll go over in a bit more detail.
Dialogue: 1,0:06:19.14,0:06:22.66,中,,0,0,0,,我会给出时间线 与每个作业时长
Dialogue: 2,0:06:19.14,0:06:22.66,英,,0,0,0,,I wanna give an idea for the timeline and how long things took.
Dialogue: 1,0:06:22.84,0:06:24.27,中,,0,0,0,,而之后三个任务 我会快速略过 让大家有个概念即可
Dialogue: 2,0:06:22.84,0:06:24.27,英,,0,0,0,,And then for the next three missions,
Dialogue: 1,0:06:24.27,0:06:27.42,中,,0,0,0,,而之后三个任务 我会快速略过 让大家有个概念即可
Dialogue: 2,0:06:24.27,0:06:27.42,英,,0,0,0,,we'll go over just a little bit quicker once we get the right idea.
Dialogue: 1,0:06:31.06,0:06:35.88,中,,0,0,0,,我要介绍的第一个任务是1998年12月的STS-88
Dialogue: 2,0:06:31.06,0:06:35.88,英,,0,0,0,,The first mission we'll talk about is STS-88 in December of 1998.
Dialogue: 1,0:06:35.95,0:06:39.06,中,,0,0,0,,"STS"全称"太空运输系统"
Dialogue: 2,0:06:35.95,0:06:39.06,英,,0,0,0,,And the STS stands for Space Transportation System.
Dialogue: 1,0:06:39.06,0:06:41.93,中,,0,0,0,,所有航天飞机任务都由这三个字母开头
Dialogue: 2,0:06:39.06,0:06:41.93,英,,0,0,0,,All shuttle missions started with these three letters.
Dialogue: 1,0:06:42.86,0:06:46.17,中,,0,0,0,,该任务是航天飞机执行的首个国际空间站任务
Dialogue: 2,0:06:42.86,0:06:46.17,英,,0,0,0,,This was the first shuttle mission to the International Space Station.
Dialogue: 1,0:06:46.62,0:06:49.22,中,,0,0,0,,此时 空间站只有一个舱段
Dialogue: 2,0:06:46.62,0:06:49.22,英,,0,0,0,,At this time, the station had only one piece.
Dialogue: 1,0:06:49.34,0:06:53.27,中,,0,0,0,,俄罗斯的曙光号功能货仓独自绕地球飞行
Dialogue: 2,0:06:49.34,0:06:53.27,英,,0,0,0,,It was the Russian module Zarya orbiting the earth all by itself.
Dialogue: 1,0:06:54.58,0:06:57.81,中,,0,0,0,,它在整个空间站中位置如画面所示
Dialogue: 2,0:06:54.58,0:06:57.81,英,,0,0,0,,On the completed station, this is where Zarya is.
Dialogue: 1,0:06:58.58,0:07:01.51,中,,0,0,0,,而首次航天飞机任务将团结号节点舱送入太空
Dialogue: 2,0:06:58.58,0:07:01.51,英,,0,0,0,,And this first shuttle mission brought up the Unity Module.
Dialogue: 1,0:07:02.68,0:07:05.12,中,,0,0,0,,它的作用就像空间站的"集线器"一样
Dialogue: 2,0:07:02.68,0:07:05.12,英,,0,0,0,,This is kind of like the center hub of the station
Dialogue: 1,0:07:05.30,0:07:08.69,中,,0,0,0,,上面有六个停泊口可供其他舱段连接
Dialogue: 2,0:07:05.30,0:07:08.69,英,,0,0,0,,with six berthing ports where other modules can be attached.
Dialogue: 1,0:07:12.07,0:07:16.39,中,,0,0,0,,与团结号一同上天的还有PMA-1和PMA-2
Dialogue: 2,0:07:12.07,0:07:16.39,英,,0,0,0,,Unity was launched with PMA-1 and PMA-2 already attached to it.
Dialogue: 1,0:07:17.24,0:07:19.81,中,,0,0,0,,此次任务共耗时近12天
Dialogue: 2,0:07:17.24,0:07:19.81,英,,0,0,0,,This mission took almost 12 days to complete.
Dialogue: 1,0:07:20.83,0:07:25.05,中,,0,0,0,,前几天用来进行前期准备 和与曙光号交会
Dialogue: 2,0:07:20.83,0:07:25.05,英,,0,0,0,,The first few days were used to make preparations and to catch up to Zarya.
Dialogue: 1,0:07:28.41,0:07:31.65,中,,0,0,0,,任务第三天 加拿大臂开始工作
Dialogue: 2,0:07:28.41,0:07:31.65,英,,0,0,0,,On day three of the mission, the Canadarm was put to work.
Dialogue: 1,0:07:32.09,0:07:34.93,中,,0,0,0,,该从载荷舱中抓起团结号了
Dialogue: 2,0:07:32.09,0:07:34.93,英,,0,0,0,,It was time to lift Unity out of the payload bay.
Dialogue: 1,0:07:36.63,0:07:40.83,中,,0,0,0,,它将PMA-2与航天飞机对接口对接
Dialogue: 2,0:07:36.63,0:07:40.83,英,,0,0,0,,PMA-2 was then attached to the orbital docking system on the shuttle.
Dialogue: 1,0:07:41.84,0:07:46.46,中,,0,0,0,,加拿大臂可以在太空的失重环境下移动大质量物体
Dialogue: 2,0:07:41.84,0:07:46.46,英,,0,0,0,,The Canadarm can move large masses in space due to being weightless while an orbit.
Dialogue: 1,0:07:46.86,0:07:50.38,中,,0,0,0,,为了不破坏机械臂关节 移动需要非常慢
Dialogue: 2,0:07:46.86,0:07:50.38,英,,0,0,0,,It had to move very slowly to not strain the robotic joints.
Dialogue: 1,0:07:50.38,0:07:54.25,中,,0,0,0,,整个过程需要极其小心 花费数小时
Dialogue: 2,0:07:50.38,0:07:54.25,英,,0,0,0,,It took hours to complete and very careful movement .
Dialogue: 1,0:07:55.60,0:07:58.86,中,,0,0,0,,航天飞机的推进器还会启动 来辅助与舱段对接
Dialogue: 2,0:07:55.60,0:07:58.86,英,,0,0,0,,The shuttle's thrusters were fired to bring the modules together.
Dialogue: 1,0:08:03.14,0:08:07.50,中,,0,0,0,,在任务第四天 航天飞机缓慢靠近曙光号
Dialogue: 2,0:08:03.14,0:08:07.50,英,,0,0,0,,On the fourth day of the mission, the space shuttle slowly approached Zarya.
Dialogue: 1,0:08:10.32,0:08:11.92,中,,0,0,0,,然后加拿大臂捕获曙光号
Dialogue: 2,0:08:10.32,0:08:11.92,英,,0,0,0,,The Canadarm grabbed onto it,
Dialogue: 1,0:08:12.99,0:08:16.35,中,,0,0,0,,将它挪到PMA-1上方
Dialogue: 2,0:08:12.99,0:08:16.35,英,,0,0,0,,and then moved it into position above PMA-1.
Dialogue: 1,0:08:19.38,0:08:23.12,中,,0,0,0,,同样 航天飞机推进器启动 将两者对接起来
Dialogue: 2,0:08:19.38,0:08:23.12,英,,0,0,0,,Again, the shuttle's thrusters were fired to bring the modules together.
Dialogue: 1,0:08:24.63,0:08:28.59,中,,0,0,0,,在乘组可以进入空间站前 还需要几天的准备
Dialogue: 2,0:08:24.63,0:08:28.59,英,,0,0,0,,It took a few more days of preparation before they could go inside the station.
Dialogue: 1,0:08:29.18,0:08:33.54,中,,0,0,0,,他们穿上舱外宇航服 进行了两次太空行走
Dialogue: 2,0:08:29.18,0:08:33.54,英,,0,0,0,,There were two EVAs where they get into their spacesuit and go outside the station.
Dialogue: 1,0:08:35.00,0:08:38.97,中,,0,0,0,,在舱段外部连接了线缆 安装了天线
Dialogue: 2,0:08:35.00,0:08:38.97,英,,0,0,0,,They connected cables and installed antennas on the outside of the station.
Dialogue: 1,0:08:40.65,0:08:43.89,中,,0,0,0,,加拿大臂还用来辅助宇航员在舱外作业时的移动
Dialogue: 2,0:08:40.65,0:08:43.89,英,,0,0,0,,The Canadarm was used to help move the astronauts around.
Dialogue: 1,0:08:46.40,0:08:51.09,中,,0,0,0,,任务第八天 他们首次打开了舱门 进入了国际空间站
Dialogue: 2,0:08:46.40,0:08:51.09,英,,0,0,0,,On the eighth day of the mission, they opened the hatch and entered the station for the first time.
Dialogue: 1,0:08:52.34,0:08:54.64,中,,0,0,0,,他们只在空间站内驻留了大约一天
Dialogue: 2,0:08:52.34,0:08:54.64,英,,0,0,0,,They only stayed inside for about a day,
Dialogue: 1,0:08:54.81,0:08:57.74,中,,0,0,0,,刚好能做些检查 并为下次任务做准备
Dialogue: 2,0:08:54.81,0:08:57.74,英,,0,0,0,,just enough to check things out and prepare it for the next mission.
Dialogue: 1,0:08:59.56,0:09:03.99,中,,0,0,0,,任务第十天 乘组再次执行一次太空行走 完成最后的安装工作
Dialogue: 2,0:08:59.56,0:09:03.99,英,,0,0,0,,On the 10th day of the mission, there was one more EVA to finish the installation.
Dialogue: 1,0:09:06.22,0:09:10.35,中,,0,0,0,,任务第十一天 航天飞机与国际空间站分离
Dialogue: 2,0:09:06.22,0:09:10.35,英,,0,0,0,,Then on the 11th day of the mission, the shuttle undocked from the ISS.
Dialogue: 1,0:09:11.33,0:09:13.58,中,,0,0,0,,此时 空间站上还没有长期驻留的宇航员
Dialogue: 2,0:09:11.33,0:09:13.58,英,,0,0,0,,At this point, there was no permanent crew yet.
Dialogue: 1,0:09:13.58,0:09:15.21,中,,0,0,0,,空间站还太小
Dialogue: 2,0:09:13.58,0:09:15.21,英,,0,0,0,,The station was too small.
Dialogue: 1,0:09:15.39,0:09:19.44,中,,0,0,0,,团结号和曙光号共同无人飞行了几个月的时间
Dialogue: 2,0:09:15.39,0:09:19.44,英,,0,0,0,,Unity and Zarya orbited all by themselves for the next few months,
Dialogue: 1,0:09:19.54,0:09:23.13,中,,0,0,0,,当然 一切都是在地面任务控制中心的掌握中
Dialogue: 2,0:09:19.54,0:09:23.13,英,,0,0,0,,of course, all while being monitored by mission control back on Earth.
Dialogue: 1,0:09:24.20,0:09:26.73,中,,0,0,0,,我们把时间快进几年
Dialogue: 2,0:09:24.20,0:09:26.73,英,,0,0,0,,Now we'll fast forward just a few years in time.
Dialogue: 1,0:09:32.30,0:09:34.40,中,,0,0,0,,现在国际空间站又新增了几个舱段
Dialogue: 2,0:09:32.30,0:09:34.40,英,,0,0,0,,The station had a few more modules,
Dialogue: 1,0:09:34.40,0:09:37.74,中,,0,0,0,,上面还有三名宇航员生活
Dialogue: 2,0:09:34.40,0:09:37.74,英,,0,0,0,,and there were three crew members living on board the station.
Dialogue: 1,0:09:39.67,0:09:44.88,中,,0,0,0,,我们要讲的下个任务是2001年2月的STS-98
Dialogue: 2,0:09:39.67,0:09:44.88,英,,0,0,0,,The next mission we'll talk about is STS-98 in February of 2001.
Dialogue: 1,0:09:45.62,0:09:47.72,中,,0,0,0,,完工的空间站是这样的
Dialogue: 2,0:09:45.62,0:09:47.72,英,,0,0,0,,So here's our completed station.
Dialogue: 1,0:09:48.03,0:09:51.39,中,,0,0,0,,而STS-98之前它长这样
Dialogue: 2,0:09:48.03,0:09:51.39,英,,0,0,0,,Here's what it looked like right before STS-98.
Dialogue: 1,0:09:51.63,0:09:53.98,中,,0,0,0,,此次任务为空间站带来了命运号实验舱
Dialogue: 2,0:09:51.63,0:09:53.98,英,,0,0,0,,This mission brought up the Destiny Module.
Dialogue: 1,0:09:56.54,0:09:59.40,中,,0,0,0,,STS-98任务持续13天
Dialogue: 2,0:09:56.54,0:09:59.40,英,,0,0,0,,STS-98 lasted for 13 days,
Dialogue: 1,0:09:59.87,0:10:03.00,中,,0,0,0,,其中只有6天是与空间站对接的状态
Dialogue: 2,0:09:59.87,0:10:03.00,英,,0,0,0,,but they were attached to the station for only six of those days.
Dialogue: 1,0:10:03.43,0:10:07.49,中,,0,0,0,,航天飞机与国际空间站底部 径向向内的PMA-3对接口对接
Dialogue: 2,0:10:03.43,0:10:07.49,英,,0,0,0,,They docked a PMA-3 on the nadir, or bottom side of the station.
Dialogue: 1,0:10:08.32,0:10:10.89,中,,0,0,0,,加拿大臂捕获PMA-2
Dialogue: 2,0:10:08.32,0:10:10.89,英,,0,0,0,,The Canadarm was used to grab onto PMA-2
Dialogue: 1,0:10:10.89,0:10:14.04,中,,0,0,0,,并把它暂时置于Z1桁架上
Dialogue: 2,0:10:10.89,0:10:14.04,英,,0,0,0,,and relocate it to the side of the Z1 Truss.
Dialogue: 1,0:10:16.02,0:10:20.29,中,,0,0,0,,随后加拿大臂拿出载荷舱中的命运号
Dialogue: 2,0:10:16.02,0:10:20.29,英,,0,0,0,,Then the arm was used to lift the Destiny Module out of the payload bay,
Dialogue: 1,0:10:20.29,0:10:23.50,中,,0,0,0,,慢慢翻转180度
Dialogue: 2,0:10:20.29,0:10:23.50,英,,0,0,0,,slowly flip it 180 degrees,
Dialogue: 1,0:10:24.03,0:10:27.54,中,,0,0,0,,并将它与团结号的前向停泊口对接
Dialogue: 2,0:10:24.03,0:10:27.54,英,,0,0,0,,and then attach it to the forward berthing port on Unity.
Dialogue: 1,0:10:27.62,0:10:32.68,中,,0,0,0,,这一操作花费了数小时 需要极其小心地移动 防止损坏设备
Dialogue: 2,0:10:27.62,0:10:32.68,英,,0,0,0,,This took hours to complete and very careful movement to make sure nothing was damaged.
Dialogue: 1,0:10:33.52,0:10:38.17,中,,0,0,0,,次日 乘组首次打开舱门 进入命运号
Dialogue: 2,0:10:33.52,0:10:38.17,英,,0,0,0,,The next day, they opened the hatches and went inside Destiny for the first time.
Dialogue: 1,0:10:39.76,0:10:44.41,中,,0,0,0,,命运号美国实验舱主要用于空间站内的科学研究
Dialogue: 2,0:10:39.76,0:10:44.41,英,,0,0,0,,US laboratory is mainly used for scientific research on board the station.
Dialogue: 1,0:10:45.94,0:10:49.84,中,,0,0,0,,随后PMA-2移动到命运号的前向停泊口
Dialogue: 2,0:10:45.94,0:10:49.84,英,,0,0,0,,PMA-2 was then relocated to the forward side of Destiny.
Dialogue: 1,0:10:54.41,0:10:56.50,中,,0,0,0,,整个任务期间 一共执行了三次太空行走
Dialogue: 2,0:10:54.41,0:10:56.50,英,,0,0,0,,The mission had three separate EVAs
Dialogue: 1,0:10:56.50,0:11:00.02,中,,0,0,0,,在空间站外进行了连接与安装设备的作业
Dialogue: 2,0:10:56.50,0:11:00.02,英,,0,0,0,,to connect and install items on the outside of the station.
Dialogue: 1,0:11:06.66,0:11:08.34,中,,0,0,0,,下一任务目标是为空间站加装一个自己的机械臂——加拿大臂2
Dialogue: 2,0:11:06.66,0:11:08.34,英,,0,0,0,,The purpose of this next mission
Dialogue: 1,0:11:08.34,0:11:12.64,中,,0,0,0,,下一任务目标是为空间站加装一个自己的机械臂——加拿大臂2
Dialogue: 2,0:11:08.34,0:11:12.64,英,,0,0,0,,was to give the station its own robotic arm called the Canadarm2.
Dialogue: 1,0:11:13.26,0:11:15.69,中,,0,0,0,,第一个加拿大臂是航天飞机上的
Dialogue: 2,0:11:13.26,0:11:15.69,英,,0,0,0,,The first Canadarm was on the space shuttle.
Dialogue: 1,0:11:15.85,0:11:19.08,中,,0,0,0,,用处很大 但它是固定在航天飞机上的
Dialogue: 2,0:11:15.85,0:11:19.08,英,,0,0,0,,Very useful, but it was permanently attached to the shuttle.
Dialogue: 1,0:11:19.19,0:11:22.20,中,,0,0,0,,所以每次航天飞机任务结束都会跟着返回地面
Dialogue: 2,0:11:19.19,0:11:22.20,英,,0,0,0,,This means it goes home at the end of a shuttle mission.
Dialogue: 1,0:11:23.34,0:11:27.95,中,,0,0,0,,而加拿大臂2现在可以在空间站上抓取重型载荷了
Dialogue: 2,0:11:23.34,0:11:27.95,英,,0,0,0,,The Canadarm2 can lift heavier loads and would now stay onboard the station,
Dialogue: 1,0:11:28.14,0:11:30.78,中,,0,0,0,,在两次航天飞机任务之间也能正常使用
Dialogue: 2,0:11:28.14,0:11:30.78,英,,0,0,0,,so it can be used in between shuttle missions.
Dialogue: 1,0:11:30.88,0:11:35.04,中,,0,0,0,,画面所示 是如今可能在空间站上发现加拿大臂2的位置
Dialogue: 2,0:11:30.88,0:11:35.04,英,,0,0,0,,Here's an example of where you might find the Canadarm2 on the station today.
Dialogue: 1,0:11:36.70,0:11:39.56,中,,0,0,0,,机械臂的两端都能与空间站相连
Dialogue: 2,0:11:36.70,0:11:39.56,英,,0,0,0,,The arm can attach to the station at either end.
Dialogue: 1,0:11:39.56,0:11:41.97,中,,0,0,0,,它们称为"锁合末端效应器"
Dialogue: 2,0:11:39.56,0:11:41.97,英,,0,0,0,,These are called Latching End Effectors.
Dialogue: 1,0:11:43.03,0:11:47.25,中,,0,0,0,,它可以与空间站上所有PDGF连接
Dialogue: 2,0:11:43.03,0:11:47.25,英,,0,0,0,,It attaches to anywhere on the station that has a power data grapple fixture.
Dialogue: 1,0:11:48.31,0:11:50.82,中,,0,0,0,,顾名思义 它可以传输电力与数据
Dialogue: 2,0:11:48.31,0:11:50.82,英,,0,0,0,,As you might guess, it provides power and data connection,
Dialogue: 1,0:11:50.82,0:11:53.45,中,,0,0,0,,因此它可以从空间站内部进行控制
Dialogue: 2,0:11:50.82,0:11:53.45,英,,0,0,0,,so it can be controlled from inside the station
Dialogue: 1,0:11:53.70,0:11:56.40,中,,0,0,0,,需要时 还可由地面任务控制中心控制
Dialogue: 2,0:11:53.70,0:11:56.40,英,,0,0,0,,and from mission control back on Earth if needed.
Dialogue: 1,0:11:57.32,0:12:01.83,中,,0,0,0,,国际空间站外部有很多PDGF
Dialogue: 2,0:11:57.32,0:12:01.83,英,,0,0,0,,These power data grapple fixtures are in many places on the outside of the station.
Dialogue: 1,0:12:03.39,0:12:07.30,中,,0,0,0,,加拿大臂2在STS-100任务中进入太空
Dialogue: 2,0:12:03.39,0:12:07.30,英,,0,0,0,,The mission that brought up the Canadarm2 was called STS-100.
Dialogue: 1,0:12:07.76,0:12:09.57,中,,0,0,0,,任务时长12天
Dialogue: 2,0:12:07.76,0:12:09.57,英,,0,0,0,,It was a 12-day mission.
Dialogue: 1,0:12:10.32,0:12:13.59,中,,0,0,0,,航天飞机与空间站前向的PMA-2对接口对接
Dialogue: 2,0:12:10.32,0:12:13.59,英,,0,0,0,,The shuttle docked to the front of the station at PMA-2.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:14.32,0:12:20.06,注,,0,0,0,,这个舱段类似于后来的货运飞船\N可以上行补给 可以下行货物\N一共有三艘 每次跟随航天飞机入轨并返回\N在轨时会暂时与空间站对接
Dialogue: 1,0:12:14.32,0:12:17.61,中,,0,0,0,,航天飞机携带了拉斐尔多用途后勤模组
Dialogue: 2,0:12:14.32,0:12:17.61,英,,0,0,0,,This carried Raffaello, a multi-purpose logistics module,
Dialogue: 1,0:12:17.61,0:12:20.06,中,,0,0,0,,它会暂时与空间站连接
Dialogue: 2,0:12:17.61,0:12:20.06,英,,0,0,0,,which would be temporarily attached to the station.
Dialogue: 1,0:12:20.39,0:12:23.34,中,,0,0,0,,第二件载荷就是加拿大臂2
Dialogue: 2,0:12:20.39,0:12:23.34,英,,0,0,0,,The second piece of cargo was the Canadarm2.
Dialogue: 1,0:12:23.66,0:12:26.66,中,,0,0,0,,它在载荷舱内是收纳在一个特制平台上的
Dialogue: 2,0:12:23.66,0:12:26.66,英,,0,0,0,,It was brought to the station on onboard a special pallet.
Dialogue: 1,0:12:28.19,0:12:33.24,中,,0,0,0,,航天飞机加拿大臂抓起平台 从载荷舱内拿出
Dialogue: 2,0:12:28.19,0:12:33.24,英,,0,0,0,,The shuttle's Canadarm grabbed onto the pallet, lifted it out of the payload bay,
Dialogue: 1,0:12:34.82,0:12:38.16,中,,0,0,0,,把平台放置在命运号上方
Dialogue: 2,0:12:34.82,0:12:38.16,英,,0,0,0,,and then attached the pallet to the top of the Destiny Module.
Dialogue: 1,0:12:39.13,0:12:42.75,中,,0,0,0,,宇航员慢慢把它展开并组装好
Dialogue: 2,0:12:39.13,0:12:42.75,英,,0,0,0,,It was slowly unfolded and put together by the astronauts.
Dialogue: 1,0:12:43.61,0:12:46.62,中,,0,0,0,,宇航员也得到了航天飞机加拿大臂的一点点帮助
Dialogue: 2,0:12:43.61,0:12:46.62,英,,0,0,0,,They also had a little help from the shuttle's Canadarm.
Dialogue: 1,0:12:48.52,0:12:52.26,中,,0,0,0,,随后 加拿大臂2首次自行移动
Dialogue: 2,0:12:48.52,0:12:52.26,英,,0,0,0,,Then the Canadarm2 was moved on its own for the first time.
Dialogue: 1,0:12:52.26,0:12:55.65,中,,0,0,0,,它最先与命运号侧面相连
Dialogue: 2,0:12:52.26,0:12:55.65,英,,0,0,0,,It was initially connected to the side of the Destiny Module.
Dialogue: 1,0:12:57.74,0:12:58.83,中,,0,0,0,,任务末尾 加拿大臂2把刚刚的平台抓起 "递给"了航天飞机加拿大臂
Dialogue: 2,0:12:57.74,0:12:58.83,英,,0,0,0,,At the end of the mission,
Dialogue: 1,0:12:58.83,0:13:03.70,中,,0,0,0,,任务末尾 加拿大臂2把刚刚的平台抓起 "递给"了航天飞机加拿大臂
Dialogue: 2,0:12:58.83,0:13:03.70,英,,0,0,0,,the Canadarm2 was used to lift the pallet and hand over to the shuttle's Canadarm.
Dialogue: 1,0:13:03.80,0:13:06.55,中,,0,0,0,,这是机械臂首次在太空中的"握手"
Dialogue: 2,0:13:03.80,0:13:06.55,英,,0,0,0,,This was the first robotic handshake in space,
Dialogue: 1,0:13:06.55,0:13:09.10,中,,0,0,0,,也有称"加拿大之握"
Dialogue: 2,0:13:06.55,0:13:09.10,英,,0,0,0,,sometimes referred to as the Canadian handshake
Dialogue: 1,0:13:09.10,0:13:11.97,中,,0,0,0,,因为两支机械臂都是由加拿大制造的
Dialogue: 2,0:13:09.10,0:13:11.97,英,,0,0,0,,because both of these arms were built by Canada.
Dialogue: 1,0:13:13.83,0:13:17.26,中,,0,0,0,,用完空置的平台随后又放回载荷舱
Dialogue: 2,0:13:13.83,0:13:17.26,英,,0,0,0,,The empty pallet was then put back into the payload bay.
Dialogue: 1,0:13:18.23,0:13:21.30,中,,0,0,0,,几天后 航天飞机与空间站分离
Dialogue: 2,0:13:18.23,0:13:21.30,英,,0,0,0,,A few days later, the shuttled undocked from the station.
Dialogue: 1,0:13:21.46,0:13:25.93,中,,0,0,0,,加拿大臂2执行了之后空间站的主要建造工作
Dialogue: 2,0:13:21.46,0:13:25.93,英,,0,0,0,,The Canadarm2 was essential for constructing the rest of the space station.
Dialogue: 1,0:13:27.94,0:13:32.27,中,,0,0,0,,本期视频最后想介绍的任务是STS-104
Dialogue: 2,0:13:27.94,0:13:32.27,英,,0,0,0,,The last mission that I wanna show in this video is STS-104.
Dialogue: 1,0:13:33.71,0:13:35.87,中,,0,0,0,,画面中是完工的空间站
Dialogue: 2,0:13:33.71,0:13:35.87,英,,0,0,0,,So here's the completed station,
Dialogue: 1,0:13:36.27,0:13:40.18,中,,0,0,0,,而STS-104任务前长这样
Dialogue: 2,0:13:36.27,0:13:40.18,英,,0,0,0,,and here's what it looked like right before STS-104.
Dialogue: 1,0:13:40.57,0:13:43.23,中,,0,0,0,,此次任务为空间站带来了寻求号气密舱
Dialogue: 2,0:13:40.57,0:13:43.23,英,,0,0,0,,This mission brought up the Quest Airlock.
Dialogue: 1,0:13:45.34,0:13:47.89,中,,0,0,0,,任务时长近13天
Dialogue: 2,0:13:45.34,0:13:47.89,英,,0,0,0,,The mission lasted for almost 13 days.
Dialogue: 1,0:13:47.89,0:13:51.52,中,,0,0,0,,航天飞机再次与空间站前向PMA-2对接口对接
Dialogue: 2,0:13:47.89,0:13:51.52,英,,0,0,0,,Once again, docking to the front of the station at PMA-2.
Dialogue: 1,0:13:52.06,0:13:56.36,中,,0,0,0,,这是他们首次使用加拿大臂2来建造空间站
Dialogue: 2,0:13:52.06,0:13:56.36,英,,0,0,0,,This was the first time they used the Canadarm2 to help construct the station.
Dialogue: 1,0:13:56.83,0:14:02.58,中,,0,0,0,,它把寻求号气密舱缓慢移动到团结号的右舷处
Dialogue: 2,0:13:56.83,0:14:02.58,英,,0,0,0,,The Quest Airlock was slowly moved into position on the starboard side of the Unity Module.
Dialogue: 1,0:14:03.98,0:14:08.01,中,,0,0,0,,两位宇航员此时已准备好辅助新舱段的安装工作
Dialogue: 2,0:14:03.98,0:14:08.01,英,,0,0,0,,Two of the astronauts were in position ready to help install the new module.
Dialogue: 1,0:14:09.69,0:14:13.86,中,,0,0,0,,寻求号安装好后 该安装高压储气罐了
Dialogue: 2,0:14:09.69,0:14:13.86,英,,0,0,0,,Once Quest was installed, it was time for the high pressure gas tanks.
Dialogue: 1,0:14:15.94,0:14:19.56,中,,0,0,0,,高压储气罐同样使用加拿大臂2移动
Dialogue: 2,0:14:15.94,0:14:19.56,英,,0,0,0,,Once again, the Canadarm2 was used to move the tanks around.
Dialogue: 1,0:14:20.84,0:14:23.72,中,,0,0,0,,宇航员辅助储气罐移动到正确位置
Dialogue: 2,0:14:20.84,0:14:23.72,英,,0,0,0,,The astronauts helped guide the tanks into position.
Dialogue: 1,0:14:31.21,0:14:36.02,中,,0,0,0,,在此之前 宇航员只能使用航天飞机载荷舱的出口出舱
Dialogue: 2,0:14:31.21,0:14:36.02,英,,0,0,0,,Up until this point, they could only perform spacewalks from the shuttle's payload bay,
Dialogue: 1,0:14:38.26,0:14:40.89,中,,0,0,0,,但有了寻求号气密舱后 他们就多了一个选择
Dialogue: 2,0:14:38.26,0:14:40.89,英,,0,0,0,,but the Quest Airlock gave them another option.
Dialogue: 1,0:14:42.00,0:14:44.06,中,,0,0,0,,矮粗的部分是"装备段"
Dialogue: 2,0:14:42.00,0:14:44.06,英,,0,0,0,,This part is called the equipment lock,
Dialogue: 1,0:14:44.06,0:14:46.06,中,,0,0,0,,细长部分是"乘员段"
Dialogue: 2,0:14:44.06,0:14:46.06,英,,0,0,0,,and this part is called the crew lock.
Dialogue: 1,0:14:47.11,0:14:49.56,中,,0,0,0,,宇航员在当中穿好舱外宇航服后
Dialogue: 2,0:14:47.11,0:14:49.56,英,,0,0,0,,Once the astronauts are inside of their spacesuits,
Dialogue: 1,0:14:49.76,0:14:53.55,中,,0,0,0,,关好内部舱门 乘员段减压
Dialogue: 2,0:14:49.76,0:14:53.55,英,,0,0,0,,the hatch is closed, and the crew lock is depressurized.
Dialogue: 1,0:14:53.78,0:14:56.22,中,,0,0,0,,即抽掉其中的所有空气
Dialogue: 2,0:14:53.78,0:14:56.22,英,,0,0,0,,This means that all the air is pumped out.
Dialogue: 1,0:14:57.00,0:14:59.04,中,,0,0,0,,然后打开气密舱舱门
Dialogue: 2,0:14:57.00,0:14:59.04,英,,0,0,0,,Now the airlock hatch is opened,
Dialogue: 1,0:14:59.16,0:15:01.45,中,,0,0,0,,再打开外部的隔热罩
Dialogue: 2,0:14:59.16,0:15:01.45,英,,0,0,0,,and then the thermal cover on the outside.
Dialogue: 1,0:15:01.86,0:15:03.42,中,,0,0,0,,舱门开口为径向向内
Dialogue: 2,0:15:01.86,0:15:03.42,英,,0,0,0,,The opening points straight down.
Dialogue: 1,0:15:03.42,0:15:06.66,中,,0,0,0,,所以宇航员开门后第一眼是空间站下方的地球
Dialogue: 2,0:15:03.42,0:15:06.66,英,,0,0,0,,So the first thing they see is the Earth right beneath them.
Dialogue: 1,0:15:09.43,0:15:12.41,中,,0,0,0,,本期视频总结了航天飞机的四次任务
Dialogue: 2,0:15:09.43,0:15:12.41,英,,0,0,0,,This video summarized four separate shuttle missions,
Dialogue: 1,0:15:12.41,0:15:16.87,中,,0,0,0,,让大家能更好了解国际空间站的建设经历
Dialogue: 2,0:15:12.41,0:15:16.87,英,,0,0,0,,just to give you a better idea of what it took to construct the International Space Station.
Dialogue: 1,0:15:17.26,0:15:19.02,中,,0,0,0,,这些还只是早期阶段
Dialogue: 2,0:15:17.26,0:15:19.02,英,,0,0,0,,This was just the early stages,
Dialogue: 1,0:15:19.02,0:15:21.31,中,,0,0,0,,国际空间站的建设还有很多工作要完成
Dialogue: 2,0:15:19.02,0:15:21.31,英,,0,0,0,,and there's a lot more to the construction.
Dialogue: 1,0:15:21.43,0:15:23.72,中,,0,0,0,,我或许会在未来视频中继续为大家介绍
Dialogue: 2,0:15:21.43,0:15:23.72,英,,0,0,0,,Maybe we'll cover that in a future video.
Dialogue: 1,0:15:23.91,0:15:25.98,中,,0,0,0,,我是Jared 感谢观看
Dialogue: 2,0:15:23.91,0:15:25.98,英,,0,0,0,,My name's Jared. Thanks for watching.
